actions.text: The House Committee on Rules reported an original measure, H. Rept. 102-976, by Mr. Moakley.

Rule provides for consideration of the conference report to S. 2532. Waiving all points of order against the conference report and against its consideration. Conference report shall be considered as read when called up.
Placed on the House Calendar, Calendar No. 226.
DEBATE - The House proceeded with one hour of debate.
The previous question was ordered without objection.
On agreeing to the resolution Agreed to by voice vote.
Motion to reconsider laid on the table Agreed to without objection.

official_title: Waiving points of order against the conference report to accompany the bill (S. 2532) entitled the "Freedom for Russia and Emerging Eurasian Democracies and Open Markets Support Act", and against the consideration of such conference report.

summary.text: Waives points of order against the consideration of the conference report on S. 2532 (assistance for the independent states of the former Soviet Union).
